In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris speaks at Drake University in Des Moines, Iowa, addressing the issue of abortion rights and the erosion of rights happening across the country. She discusses the recent six-week abortion ban in Iowa and the larger fight for reproductive rights. Harris emphasizes the importance of respecting women's bodily autonomy and their right to make decisions about their own bodies. She criticizes the hypocrisy of lawmakers who claim to care about mothers and children but ignore issues like maternal mortality. Harris also highlights the need for coalition building and the power of voting to protect and restore rights. She encourages young people to lead and expresses optimism for the future despite the challenges.